It explains that Sonic Hedgehog is found notated alternatively as "Shh". It also mentions that Sonic Hedgehog is one of three proteins in the mammalian signaling pathway family called Hedgehog, the others being Desert Hedgehog (Dhh) and Indian Hedgehog (Ihh). It states that Sonic Hedgehog is the best studied ligand of the Hedgehog signaling pathway, and that it plays a key role in regulating vertebrate organogenesis, such as in the growth of digits on limbs and organization of the brain. Sonic Hedgehog is the best established example of a morphogen as defined by Lewis Wolpert\'s French flag modelâa molecule that diffuses to form a concentration gradient and has different effects on the cells of the developing embryo depending on its concentration. Sonic Hedgehog remains important in the adult. It controls cell division of adult stem cells and has been implicated in the development of some cancers.'}
